1
00:00:10,290 --> 00:00:12,010
Get ready for a poster photoshoot.

2
00:00:12,010 --> 00:00:14,390
Our group is going to be a hit.

3
00:00:14,390 --> 00:00:16,550
You’re really going viral.

4
00:00:16,550 --> 00:00:19,670
Here, the views have already passed 100,000.

5
00:00:19,670 --> 00:00:23,170
I’m afraid that I’m not a good leader.

6
00:00:23,170 --> 00:00:25,560
Our group’s already hanging by a thread.

7
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:27,070
This is gonna make things worse.

8
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:30,320
We should increase our fanbase

9
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:31,610
with the trial dating thing.

10
00:00:31,610 --> 00:00:34,200
Cutter with Yu. Jeng with Mai.

11
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,570
Have you ever been to Talad Noi?

12
00:00:35,570 --> 00:00:36,490
Not yet.

13
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:41,420
I’ll take you there.

14
00:01:46,110 --> 00:01:48,110
(Welcome to Talad Noi.)

15
00:01:48,670 --> 00:01:49,970
Have you ever been here?

16
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,530
Yeah, I like hanging out around here.

17
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:54,970
I’ve never been here before.

18
00:01:54,970 --> 00:01:56,650
It’s so photogenic.

19
00:01:57,090 --> 00:01:58,950
Hey, can you take a pic for me?

20
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:01,300
-Who’s more handsome?
-One,

21
00:02:01,750 --> 00:02:02,810
two, three.

22
00:02:04,470 --> 00:02:05,400
Who’s more handsome?

23
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,630
Boo.

24
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:12,500
This isn’t giving like Cutter said.

25
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:14,790
But this guy…

26
00:02:15,250 --> 00:02:16,020
is cute.

27
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:24,280
Go on. It’s your turn.

28
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:31,350
Let me see how Mr. Handsome poses.

29
00:02:32,810 --> 00:02:33,730
Alright.

30
00:02:34,410 --> 00:02:35,970
One, two, three.

31
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:41,260
So? Do I look handsome?

32
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:42,460
Well.

33
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:45,460
A little less handsome than me.

34
00:02:49,930 --> 00:02:52,190
I won’t give in to anyone else

35
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,790
but you, Leader.

36
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:04,410
Wanna take a photo together?

37
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:06,200
How about over there?

38
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:11,380
Alright, one, two.

39
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:15,270
Can you smile a little?

40
00:03:15,270 --> 00:03:16,640
Let’s try again. Give me a smile.

41
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:17,630
Okay.

42
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:20,150
One, two, three.

43
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,720
Let me see.

44
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:25,120
Much better.

45
00:03:25,290 --> 00:03:26,260
See?

46
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:29,770
You look so cute when you smile.

47
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,770
Smile a little more.

48
00:03:34,050 --> 00:03:36,010
My smile is already right in front of me.

49
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:42,160
Don’t go smiling like that at just anyone,

50
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:43,670
got it?

51
00:03:54,329 --> 00:03:55,500
Whoa, whoa.

52
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:56,700
Wow.

53
00:04:08,820 --> 00:04:10,450
Why do you look so happy?

54
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,600
Because this cartoon is funny.

55
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:17,110
I used to watch it when I was a kid.

56
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:18,950
Never thought I’d get to watch it again.

57
00:04:19,540 --> 00:04:21,810
It makes me so nostalgic.

58
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:25,170
Sometimes I’m jealous of you.

59
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:27,810
Jealous of what?

60
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:32,000
You get excited about everything.

61
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:38,360
Like the whole world is full of wonders to you.

62
00:04:39,810 --> 00:04:40,730
What about you?

63
00:04:41,659 --> 00:04:42,870
Don’t you get excited?

64
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:48,120
Or are you speaking from experience?

65
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:50,180
How?

66
00:04:51,850 --> 00:04:52,930
Well.

67
00:04:53,540 --> 00:04:56,460
If you keep comparing everything

68
00:04:57,450 --> 00:04:59,290
to what you’ve already experienced,

69
00:04:59,290 --> 00:05:02,240
nothing will feel exciting.

70
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:05,440
You’ll only end up disappointed.

71
00:05:05,670 --> 00:05:06,520
But…

72
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:10,240
If life has been rough,

73
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:14,120
just think of it as experience

74
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:17,210
because there's always a new beginning

75
00:05:18,030 --> 00:05:19,700
after every failure.

76
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:25,120
I wish that boy could think like you.

77
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:27,880
He fought for his dream all by himself,

78
00:05:28,540 --> 00:05:32,020
but the adults looked down on him,

79
00:05:32,610 --> 00:05:35,840
and sent him back for no reason in the end.

80
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:38,840
He fought for 10 years.

81
00:05:39,890 --> 00:05:41,460
All he could do

82
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,230
was keep doing what he loved

83
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:47,230
without chasing that dream anymore.

84
00:05:49,180 --> 00:05:50,760
Until he met someone.

85
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,840
Someone who gave everything to his dream.

86
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:00,110
And that person’s smile

87
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:03,660
made the boy dream again.

88
00:06:06,420 --> 00:06:07,810
That person is…

89
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,550
Hello, Tian.

90
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:23,080
I’m heading back.

91
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,550
Alright, I’ll come see you.

92
00:06:26,130 --> 00:06:28,390
Okay. See you.

93
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:29,610
I'm already in touch with them.

94
00:07:29,610 --> 00:07:33,600
I guarantee our client willl love it.

95
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:36,510
Yes, I'm giving it my all.

96
00:07:40,510 --> 00:07:43,030
Oh, Boss Si Tian.

97
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:44,980
What a coincidence.

98
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,170
Bai Liu.

99
00:07:50,990 --> 00:07:52,180
So this is

100
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:57,790
Mr. Si Tian, the owner of Ultimate Woof,

101
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,610
or should I say Ultimate Woops?

102
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,230
Boss.

103
00:08:04,530 --> 00:08:07,020
Is this the guy you mentioned?

104
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:09,440
The fake one?

105
00:08:10,030 --> 00:08:10,770
Ooh.

106
00:08:10,770 --> 00:08:13,000
His acting was terrible.

107
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:16,170
Someone should send him to acting school.

108
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:19,850
He was so fake during the live press conference.

109
00:08:19,850 --> 00:08:20,970
So it’s him?

110
00:08:22,530 --> 00:08:24,230
Fake?

111
00:08:24,610 --> 00:08:28,540
My label is the real deal.

112
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:32,470
At least we’re not some dying label

113
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:34,919
like a certain label around here.

114
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:38,270
Oh my, Shining.

115
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,620
Stay cool.

116
00:08:40,309 --> 00:08:42,409
Sorry about that, Tian.

117
00:08:42,409 --> 00:08:43,770
Don’t take it personally.

118
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:46,980
Actually, I’ve been rooting for you.

119
00:08:47,350 --> 00:08:49,350
I hope your next song

120
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:52,060
becomes a huge hit.

121
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,740
Let’s go, Shining.

122
00:08:54,990 --> 00:08:57,850
We’ve to pick up our new trainee from the airport.

123
00:08:57,850 --> 00:09:00,440
I wonder if he's landed from Korea yet.

124
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,240
That’s right.

125
00:09:04,580 --> 00:09:05,740
See you later.

126
00:09:08,890 --> 00:09:10,290
Kamsahamnida.

127
00:09:10,290 --> 00:09:12,460
I better start learning Korean

128
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:14,730
since we have a Korean trainee now.

129
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,890
What a joke.

130
00:09:17,330 --> 00:09:18,490
Hmph.

131
00:09:20,990 --> 00:09:22,280
-Medyer.
-Yes?

132
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,900
I want to talk to you about the song.

133
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:26,790
Got a minute?

134
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:27,580
Of course.

135
00:09:27,810 --> 00:09:31,020
I want you to make our song go viral.

136
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:34,520
I heard the boys talk about a random dance at Siam.

137
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:39,070
Maybe we can work something out with our sponsor.

138
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:40,630
Boss.

139
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,920
What if nobody joins?

140
00:09:44,940 --> 00:09:46,130
We have to try.

141
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:48,130
There’s nothing to lose.

142
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:51,580
I’ll leave you to it.

143
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:54,570
Don’t worry. I’ll do my best.

144
00:09:54,570 --> 00:09:58,370
I’ll make our label go viral and iconic, Boss.

145
00:09:58,370 --> 00:10:00,770
Good. I’m counting on you.

146
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,580
I don’t want our label to fail.

147
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:05,660
Honestly,

148
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:09,550
I never wanted to compete with that label.

149
00:10:10,330 --> 00:10:11,440
I just hoped

150
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:16,330
they’d think we're decent.

151
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,910
Don’t worry, Boss.

152
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,440
This time, underdogs like us

153
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:24,310
are gonna take down that giant.

154
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:27,920
Let’s have a drink.

155
00:10:29,410 --> 00:10:31,830
Alright, I’ll take care of it.

156
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,580
Everything will be perfect.

157
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:38,070
Our marketing plan’s going well.

158
00:10:38,070 --> 00:10:39,680
Thank you for your hard work.

159
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:41,200
No problem.

160
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,180
Ah!

161
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:45,130
Who is this?

162
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:46,340
I’m scared.

163
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:48,060
Don’t be scared. I’m your friend.

164
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:49,720
Look closely.

165
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:53,960
Take the mask off. There’s no one here.

166
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,820
Take it off!

167
00:10:58,180 --> 00:10:59,340
I already did!

168
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:00,980
Okay.

169
00:11:00,980 --> 00:11:03,340
Let me tell you something.

170
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:05,620
You don’t even need the mask.

171
00:11:05,620 --> 00:11:09,110
Just wipe off your makeup,

172
00:11:09,110 --> 00:11:12,020
and people will think you’re a man.

173
00:11:12,020 --> 00:11:13,040
No one will recognize you.

174
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:15,050
Hey, show some respect to my makeup.

175
00:11:15,050 --> 00:11:15,560
Why?

176
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:17,340
Girl, I look this gorgeous.

177
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:18,570
Gorgeous where?

178
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:19,800
What about you?

179
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,340
You’re not prettier than me.

180
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:24,630
-Big talk.
-Hey!

181
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:26,490
You two are at it again.

182
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:27,470
Seriously.

183
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:29,500
Can’t you stop fighting for a day?

184
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:32,340
Everyone’s gonna notice us at this rate.

185
00:11:32,730 --> 00:11:35,590
And you’ve been gone for a while. Let’s get to the point.

186
00:11:35,590 --> 00:11:37,340
What’s their next move?

187
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:40,000
I checked it out.

188
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:42,090
They’re going to do a random dance.

189
00:11:42,090 --> 00:11:43,230
A random dance?

190
00:11:43,230 --> 00:11:44,110
Yeah.

191
00:11:44,110 --> 00:11:45,430
A random dance.

192
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:47,510
They’ll play the songs from their label

193
00:11:47,510 --> 00:11:49,190
and let random people dance.

194
00:11:49,190 --> 00:11:51,200
It’s a promo event.

195
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:53,770
Good idea.

196
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:55,540
But it’s kinda risky.

197
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:59,870
What if nobody shows up to dance?

198
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:03,340
They said they’re going all in.

199
00:12:03,340 --> 00:12:06,600
Even if they fail, they don’t care.

200
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:10,480
I hope it works out for them.

201
00:12:12,570 --> 00:12:14,770
Young master, I’ve got something to tell you.

202
00:12:14,770 --> 00:12:15,770
What is it?

203
00:12:15,770 --> 00:12:17,510
Si Tian said

204
00:12:17,510 --> 00:12:20,030
he never wanted to compete with you.

205
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:22,850
He just wanted to prove himself.

206
00:12:22,850 --> 00:12:26,420
And from the way he looked at you,

207
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:28,660
I swear he still has feelings for you.

208
00:12:32,430 --> 00:12:35,260
You do too?

209
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,980
What feelings? Don't be silly.

210
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,180
Fine, fine.

211
00:12:40,180 --> 00:12:42,870
So how do you wanna help Si Tian?

212
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:44,990
Any ideas?

213
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:51,380
Oh.

214
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:53,280
I just thought of one.

215
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:54,510
You’re amazing.

216
00:12:54,810 --> 00:12:56,880
You’re always so quick witted.

217
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:03,600
Where is P’Medyer?

218
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,510
She told us to meet here, but she isn’t here.

219
00:13:07,210 --> 00:13:09,560
She’s probably finding the location for us.

220
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:18,870
Hey.

221
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:20,870
Hey.

222
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:23,250
Guys.

223
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,110
Don’t you think…

224
00:13:26,490 --> 00:13:27,770
something feels off today?

225
00:13:28,870 --> 00:13:32,920
Why’s everyone eating bitter melon?

226
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:36,130
Is it some new Chinese trend?

227
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:38,160
Did I miss it?

228
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,100
Wait!

229
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:42,650
Is our song popular now?

230
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:43,780
Wow.

231
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:46,780
Then tonight I’m checking the market

232
00:13:46,780 --> 00:13:48,150
to see if bitter melon’s sold out.

233
00:13:48,510 --> 00:13:49,690
I think it’s real.

234
00:13:49,690 --> 00:13:51,090
That’d be amazing.

235
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:53,360
We started a new trend.

236
00:13:54,780 --> 00:13:56,080
I hope so.

237
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:59,500
We’ll know soon enough.

238
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,980
Just wait for tonight.

239
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:03,170
If people come out and dance to our song,

240
00:14:03,390 --> 00:14:04,990
then it’s real.

241
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,160
Guys.

242
00:14:08,190 --> 00:14:09,930
The venue’s all set. Let’s go.

243
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:12,320
Everything’s ready.

244
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:15,480
It’s our time to shine. Let’s go!

245
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,480
Let’s do this, guys!

246
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,680
Yay!

247
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,480
Dang.

248
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,770
So many people.

249
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,140
Whoa.

250
00:14:38,770 --> 00:14:40,480
I haven't danced like this in a while.

251
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:47,200
Nervous?

252
00:14:47,770 --> 00:14:48,670
Yeah.

253
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:49,580
So many people.

254
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,620
Just hold my hand.

255
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:57,270
You’ll feel better.

256
00:15:01,070 --> 00:15:02,200
You’re really nervous, huh?

257
00:15:03,850 --> 00:15:04,980
Your hand’s so sweaty.

258
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:06,250
Shut up.

259
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:12,040
That’s enough. Someone will see us.

260
00:15:14,350 --> 00:15:15,390
No one’s looking.

261
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:19,480
Alright, everyone.

262
00:15:20,630 --> 00:15:21,600
Ready?

263
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:22,900
Ready!

264
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:25,270
I already added our song to the queue.

265
00:15:25,780 --> 00:15:27,810
We’ll dance to other songs first,

266
00:15:28,350 --> 00:15:30,720
then our song will come next.

267
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:32,360
Okay?

268
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:32,930
Yep.

269
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:33,960
Are you ready?

270
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:34,810
Yes!

271
00:15:34,810 --> 00:15:38,480
Before we begin, I’ve a little gift for you all.

272
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,090
What is it?

273
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:42,190
Whoa!

274
00:15:42,950 --> 00:15:45,720
No way!

275
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:48,480
These are Champion shirts.

276
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,200
I talked to the brand,

277
00:15:50,770 --> 00:15:55,010
and they like how this event motivates young people.

278
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,080
Here. Put them on.

279
00:15:58,590 --> 00:15:59,800
Whoa, these are sick.

280
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,480
Thank you.

281
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,290
Once you’re done changing, bring them back to me.

282
00:16:02,290 --> 00:16:05,330
Medyer asked me to take care of them for you.

283
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:08,100
Oh.

284
00:16:08,580 --> 00:16:11,480
Where is Medyer?

285
00:16:12,190 --> 00:16:15,300
She’s meeting with a client,

286
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:19,280
trying to get our group on Hiwwhee channel.

287
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,070
Nice.

288
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:26,390
Hiring her was the right call.

289
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:28,730
She’s such a pro.

290
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:39,360
I’m sure we’re gonna be a hit.

291
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,580
Alright, let’s go get changed.

292
00:16:42,090 --> 00:16:45,380
I’m happy we can wear something this cool.

293
00:16:47,070 --> 00:16:48,000
Great job.

294
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,480
Excuse us.

295
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,210
-Sorry.
-A superstar is coming.

296
00:17:10,390 --> 00:17:11,480
The first song’s on.

297
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:13,650
I can dance this one.

298
00:17:14,609 --> 00:17:16,339
Calm down.

299
00:17:31,170 --> 00:17:33,190
I want to be Mabelz!

300
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,370
Mai.

301
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:39,130
Hm?

302
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:42,340
Are people gonna dance to our song?

303
00:17:43,290 --> 00:17:44,190
Of course.

304
00:17:44,810 --> 00:17:45,920
Our song’s quite popular.

305
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,330
It’s Toon Alie Blackcobra.

306
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,690
I wanna dance already.

307
00:18:13,060 --> 00:18:13,770
Yo!

308
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:15,370
It’s our song!

309
00:18:15,710 --> 00:18:17,090
This is our moment!

310
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,140
But…

311
00:18:21,030 --> 00:18:22,640
Why isn’t anyone coming out?

312
00:18:32,130 --> 00:18:34,200
Someone will come soon, Jeng.

313
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:36,700
Jeng.

314
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:48,990
Just one look into your eyes

315
00:18:48,990 --> 00:18:51,340
I almost lose my mind

316
00:18:51,340 --> 00:18:55,840
I keep thinking about you every single night

317
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:04,750
Be happy to…

318
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:08,050
Hey, do you eat bitter melon?

319
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:10,480
Wanna be my love?

320
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:12,480
I can’t look away from you

321
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,350
I’m going crazy because…

322
00:19:14,350 --> 00:19:17,280
Hey, are you Google?

323
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:19,190
You can find anything

324
00:19:19,190 --> 00:19:20,260
What should we do?

325
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,310
Should we go out?

326
00:19:22,310 --> 00:19:23,210
Whatever!

327
00:19:23,210 --> 00:19:24,130
Hey, bro!

328
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,120
Be happy to…

329
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:35,390
Hey, do you eat bitter melon?

330
00:19:35,390 --> 00:19:37,800
Wanna be my love?

331
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,920
I can’t look away from you

332
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:41,690
I’m going crazy because…

333
00:19:41,690 --> 00:19:44,640
Hey, are you Google?

334
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:47,990
You can find anything

335
00:19:47,990 --> 00:19:50,110
But you’re my everything

336
00:19:50,110 --> 00:19:51,480
I’m so fluttered because of (you)

337
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,230
How could they dance?

338
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:23,480
I’ve never heard the song. Do you know it?

339
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:24,480
Can you dance to it?

340
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:25,760
Do you know this one?

341
00:20:31,170 --> 00:20:34,130
There are so many people here.

342
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:34,980
For real.

343
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:37,480
Too bad no one danced to our song.

344
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:38,480
Hey.

345
00:20:38,820 --> 00:20:40,010
You guys did great.

346
00:20:40,310 --> 00:20:42,570
Didn’t our song do well, Boss?

347
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,640
You all did great.

348
00:20:51,630 --> 00:20:52,370
Guys.

349
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,300
Huh?

350
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:54,940
I’ll go back first.

351
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:56,480
Okay.

352
00:20:58,670 --> 00:20:59,910
What’s up with him?

353
00:21:00,730 --> 00:21:01,480
Jeng?

354
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:03,900
Jeng!

355
00:21:07,670 --> 00:21:10,040
He’s leaving too?

356
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:14,980
I’m so tired.

357
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:19,130
Why is it so hard?

358
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:24,300
Everyone’s amazing.

359
00:21:26,430 --> 00:21:27,460
They really are.

360
00:21:29,260 --> 00:21:30,290
Every single one.

361
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:37,480
But I dragged them into this mess.

362
00:21:39,580 --> 00:21:40,580
Jeng.

363
00:21:43,030 --> 00:21:44,210
What are you even good at?

364
00:21:46,350 --> 00:21:47,770
You’re not good at anything.

365
00:21:50,050 --> 00:21:52,010
Everyone else isn’t a loser.

366
00:21:53,860 --> 00:21:57,070
Maybe I’m the only loser here.

367
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,060
Me.

368
00:22:02,010 --> 00:22:04,000
Jeng the loser.

369
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:09,580
Jeng!

370
00:22:10,580 --> 00:22:11,320
Jeng!

371
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:14,140
Where are you?

372
00:22:15,310 --> 00:22:16,050
Jeng!

373
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:19,910
Huh?

374
00:22:20,670 --> 00:22:21,940
Did Boss send you to look for me?

375
00:22:22,670 --> 00:22:25,470
So where are we celebrating tonight?

376
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:27,760
We’re so–

377
00:22:32,850 --> 00:22:34,350
It’s okay to cry.

378
00:22:35,780 --> 00:22:37,340
You’ve been doing well,

379
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:39,810
Leader.

380
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:56,580
Hey.

381
00:22:58,290 --> 00:22:59,680
You can leave me alone.

382
00:23:01,730 --> 00:23:03,340
Go hang out with the others.

383
00:23:04,770 --> 00:23:06,180
They’ll be looking for you.

384
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,250
I’m tougher than I look.

385
00:23:17,580 --> 00:23:18,710
I’m Jeng.

386
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,810
I'm an amazing gem, right?

387
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,180
I know,

388
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:36,800
but I don’t want you to be alone.

389
00:23:39,580 --> 00:23:40,670
Let it out, Jeng.

390
00:23:41,910 --> 00:23:43,190
Cry as much as you need.

391
00:23:45,580 --> 00:23:46,730
I’m here.

392
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:17,230
A leader

393
00:24:19,030 --> 00:24:20,720
shouldn’t be a crybaby.

394
00:24:25,710 --> 00:24:26,680
My name is Jeng,

395
00:24:30,130 --> 00:24:31,930
so I have to be the strongest gem.

396
00:24:38,820 --> 00:24:40,140
You don’t have to be the best.

397
00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:42,640
Just being you is enough.

398
00:24:53,010 --> 00:24:53,850
I’m sorry.

399
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,090
For what?

400
00:24:57,430 --> 00:24:58,090
This.

401
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:21,180
Can I kiss you again?

402
00:25:38,750 --> 00:25:39,860
What are you laughing at?

403
00:25:41,660 --> 00:25:42,950
I just got shy.

404
00:25:49,670 --> 00:25:51,520
Can you not smile like that at anyone else?

405
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:54,920
I’ll get jealous.

406
00:26:14,090 --> 00:26:15,060
Seriously,

407
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:18,060
today was just too much.

408
00:26:18,630 --> 00:26:19,480
Don’t you think?

409
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:23,180
It sucked,

410
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:25,500
but it’s not that terrible.

411
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:26,660
Really?

412
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:30,590
No one knew our dance.

413
00:26:31,730 --> 00:26:33,590
I feel like you have to face this because of me.

414
00:26:35,070 --> 00:26:36,500
Why are you blaming yourself?

415
00:26:37,620 --> 00:26:38,400
Because…

416
00:26:39,370 --> 00:26:40,870
This all started with me.

417
00:26:41,770 --> 00:26:43,840
I asked them to join the group.

418
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:48,620
I told them we’d make it.

419
00:26:49,030 --> 00:26:50,080
That we’d get famous.

420
00:26:51,290 --> 00:26:51,900
But…

421
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:55,520
Now it just feels like I wasted everyone’s time.

422
00:26:56,950 --> 00:26:57,840
That’s not true.

423
00:26:58,090 --> 00:26:58,890
Really?

424
00:27:01,180 --> 00:27:02,300
Everyone’s talented.

425
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:04,560
Yu.

426
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:06,080
Fong.

427
00:27:06,730 --> 00:27:07,700
Cutter.

428
00:27:09,470 --> 00:27:10,530
You too.

429
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:14,180
Me?

430
00:27:16,180 --> 00:27:18,520
No, I’m not good at anything.

431
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:21,050
I’m neither a great dancer,

432
00:27:21,330 --> 00:27:22,330
nor a rapper.

433
00:27:23,070 --> 00:27:24,300
My voice isn’t that good either.

434
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:26,400
And my looks…

435
00:27:27,180 --> 00:27:28,310
are nothing special.

436
00:27:29,410 --> 00:27:31,420
I’m just a jack of all trades,

437
00:27:31,870 --> 00:27:33,060
master of none.

438
00:27:35,580 --> 00:27:36,910
But you’re amazing.

439
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:38,740
You can do anything,

440
00:27:39,270 --> 00:27:40,680
and work well with the team.

441
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,730
That’s you.

442
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:44,710
How?

443
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,020
Fong is too serious.

444
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:48,960
Yu gets too nervous.

445
00:27:49,340 --> 00:27:50,880
Cutter is too confident.

446
00:27:52,700 --> 00:27:55,660
You’re the one who keeps us balanced.

447
00:28:00,460 --> 00:28:02,300
That’s how special you are, Jeng.

448
00:28:02,980 --> 00:28:04,330
My strongest little Jack.

449
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:09,180
You should be proud of yourself.

450
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:12,060
Be proud every single day.

451
00:28:12,940 --> 00:28:14,020
I’ll be watching.

452
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:20,640
That’s kinda mean.

453
00:28:21,010 --> 00:28:21,940
How?

454
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:24,970
Because…

455
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:29,610
You’re...

456
00:28:33,460 --> 00:28:34,520
making my heart race.

457
00:28:44,470 --> 00:28:45,360
Can you hear it?

458
00:28:46,810 --> 00:28:48,030
Mine is racing too.

459
00:29:02,620 --> 00:29:05,560
From now on, you don’t have to be alone anymore.

460
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:09,570
I’ll stay by your side, and not going anywhere.

461
00:29:20,310 --> 00:29:22,180
So, are you tired?

462
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:23,330
A little.

463
00:29:26,010 --> 00:29:26,800
So…

464
00:29:27,530 --> 00:29:29,610
Are you heading home, or are you going somewhere?

465
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:31,200
I don’t know.

466
00:29:33,190 --> 00:29:37,140
By the way, won’t the others wonder where we went?

467
00:29:38,130 --> 00:29:40,740
Nah, I already told Brother Tian I was coming to find you.

468
00:29:40,740 --> 00:29:42,190
And I told them to head home first.

469
00:29:42,750 --> 00:29:44,940
Wait, what did you just say?

470
00:29:45,470 --> 00:29:47,590
I told everyone to head home first.

471
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:50,420
No. I meant when you called him Brother Tian.

472
00:29:52,780 --> 00:29:53,590
Oh.

473
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:56,520
Boss Tian?

474
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:57,460
Yeah.

475
00:29:58,310 --> 00:29:59,750
I mean Boss Tian.

476
00:30:04,010 --> 00:30:04,750
Jeng.

477
00:30:04,750 --> 00:30:05,420
Hm?

478
00:30:06,540 --> 00:30:08,120
Can I steal you away for a bit?

479
00:30:09,050 --> 00:30:09,870
Where to?

480
00:31:04,170 --> 00:31:05,050
You having fun?

481
00:31:05,270 --> 00:31:06,110
Yes.

482
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:11,160
Why’d you bring me here?

483
00:31:12,410 --> 00:31:13,100
Well.

484
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:15,340
When I was a kid,

485
00:31:15,340 --> 00:31:17,130
I never got to go to an amusement park.

486
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:20,110
I never rode a roller coaster,

487
00:31:21,250 --> 00:31:22,830
a Ferris wheel,

488
00:31:24,340 --> 00:31:26,010
or even a carousel.

489
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:30,520
I just wanted to know what childhood was like.

490
00:31:31,570 --> 00:31:33,440
So you brought me here to ride the carousel?

491
00:31:33,780 --> 00:31:34,410
Yeah.

492
00:31:35,010 --> 00:31:35,880
You’re such a goof.

493
00:31:37,290 --> 00:31:40,150
I just wanted to try enjoying things like a kid.

494
00:31:41,250 --> 00:31:44,010
It’s not goofy, but it’s so much fun.

495
00:31:44,310 --> 00:31:46,660
Now we get to be kids together.

496
00:31:49,890 --> 00:31:52,410
Let’s see who’s faster.

497
00:31:52,700 --> 00:31:53,330
Deal.

498
00:31:54,110 --> 00:31:55,730
Ready? One, two, three!

499
00:31:58,630 --> 00:31:59,520
Go, my boy!

500
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,190
You’re catching up!

501
00:32:02,550 --> 00:32:03,750
No way.

502
00:32:07,770 --> 00:32:08,860
Don’t give up yet.

503
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:10,980
My horse is about to pass out.

504
00:32:11,340 --> 00:32:12,830
Yours is done for.

505
00:32:13,660 --> 00:32:14,870
It’s exhausted.

506
00:32:15,620 --> 00:32:17,680
Not just the horse, we’re exhausted too.

507
00:32:27,380 --> 00:32:28,200
Thank you

508
00:32:29,770 --> 00:32:32,250
for letting me experience childhood.

509
00:32:33,610 --> 00:32:34,390
And…

510
00:32:35,670 --> 00:32:38,450
Thanks for helping me dream again.

511
00:32:53,410 --> 00:32:55,430
Hey! Jeng’s back!

512
00:32:55,430 --> 00:32:56,910
Our leader!

513
00:32:59,180 --> 00:33:00,010
Guys.

514
00:33:01,240 --> 00:33:02,240
I’m sorry.

515
00:33:02,550 --> 00:33:03,830
Sorry for what?

516
00:33:03,830 --> 00:33:05,610
You don’t have to be sorry.

517
00:33:11,500 --> 00:33:13,010
I’m sorry too.

518
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,480
I haven’t been giving my all,

519
00:33:16,010 --> 00:33:17,870
and spent too much time at aerobics practice.

520
00:33:19,150 --> 00:33:20,470
I’m sorry too.

521
00:33:20,970 --> 00:33:23,610
I haven’t practiced enough, and I’m still not good enough.

522
00:33:24,210 --> 00:33:25,800
I’ll work harder.

523
00:33:28,170 --> 00:33:29,330
We’re all good, right?

524
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:31,450
Of course we are.

525
00:33:31,450 --> 00:33:33,900
I’m more chill than the whole random dance floor.

526
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:34,930
Aww.

527
00:33:36,710 --> 00:33:38,250
Thank you, guys.

528
00:33:40,380 --> 00:33:42,820
We’ll get them next time..

529
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:45,230
Next random dance,

530
00:33:45,230 --> 00:33:47,550
everyone’s gonna come out and dance to our song.

531
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:52,220
I turned our dance into an aerobics routine.

532
00:33:52,220 --> 00:33:53,310
A lot of people loved it.

533
00:33:53,310 --> 00:33:54,010
Really?

534
00:33:54,340 --> 00:33:55,280
Aerobics?

535
00:33:55,780 --> 00:33:57,270
Don’t underestimate the grannies.

536
00:33:59,820 --> 00:34:00,640
Guys.

537
00:34:00,900 --> 00:34:02,260
I got a good idea.

538
00:34:03,060 --> 00:34:04,270
How about this?

539
00:34:05,010 --> 00:34:08,210
Let’s target the right audience

540
00:34:08,210 --> 00:34:11,440
by going to the aerobics area

541
00:34:11,440 --> 00:34:13,429
to win the grannies over.

542
00:34:13,590 --> 00:34:15,920
I’ll borrow my mom's truck with the speakers.

543
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:17,440
Then we’ll drive around promoting us.

544
00:34:17,830 --> 00:34:19,179
What do you think?

545
00:34:19,179 --> 00:34:20,199
Great. I’m in.

546
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:22,710
I’ll bring the rescue truck too.

547
00:34:26,659 --> 00:34:30,400
Maybe we should skip that.

548
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:34,820
People might think there’s an emergency.

549
00:34:35,860 --> 00:34:38,679
My mom’s truck should be enough.

550
00:34:41,489 --> 00:34:42,389
Let’s do it.

551
00:34:55,350 --> 00:34:57,380
Can you guys help me cheer Jeng up?

552
00:35:00,220 --> 00:35:01,500
I know you’re all exhausted.

553
00:35:03,060 --> 00:35:04,610
But Jeng is too.

554
00:35:07,450 --> 00:35:09,800
He’s carrying more pressure than you think.

555
00:35:14,330 --> 00:35:15,620
I know.

556
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:18,840
Honestly,

557
00:35:19,290 --> 00:35:20,870
we should be thanking Jeng.

558
00:35:21,860 --> 00:35:25,740
He's the reason we started dreaming again.

559
00:35:26,580 --> 00:35:29,850
What doesn't kill you makes you stronger.

560
00:35:31,210 --> 00:35:32,680
This isn’t Jeng’s fault.

561
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,890
I just expected too much,

562
00:35:39,270 --> 00:35:41,760
and put too much pressure on him as our leader.

563
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:44,320
I also owe him an apology.

564
00:35:45,580 --> 00:35:47,040
I haven’t been trying hard enough.

565
00:35:47,780 --> 00:35:49,590
I promise I’ll do better.

566
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:52,110
I won’t let Jeng’s trust go to waste.

567
00:35:54,420 --> 00:35:55,720
Thanks, guys.

568
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:59,910
I know we’re a team.

569
00:36:04,310 --> 00:36:06,010
Come on, Leader.

570
00:36:08,460 --> 00:36:09,630
Let’s do this.

571
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:19,190
Hello, everyone.

572
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:21,730
Cutter the rapper is here to rock your day.

573
00:36:21,730 --> 00:36:24,730
We’d like to ask for your support.

574
00:36:24,730 --> 00:36:26,190
Please support our group.

